  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, Lucia Weston gives news. She asks Deborah, &quot;What do you think of your timid brother [the Rev. Jonas] Perkins?&quot; Lucia comments that Mrs. Maria Weston Chapman&apos;s report was accepted by the board, and &quot;it is a most excellent thing.&quot; She tells in detail about a little ruse by which Mrs. Chapman made Mr. [William B. O.?] Peabody read a notice [of a meeting?] in his church.</subfield>
